title: Studio One - 100 Albums ( Flac )
description:
Studio One has been Jamaica's most prolific recording label for more than fifty years. Clement Seymour 'Coxsone' Dodd first began producing local Jamaican artists in the mid 1950s, initially for exclusive use on his numerous sound systems. The earliest singles and albums were recorded and pressed at Federal Studios, but in 1963 Dodd opened his own recording facilities at 13 Brentford Road, Kingston - the Jamaican Recording and Publishing Studio. Studio One is the major label and the generic title for all C.S.Dodd productions. (...) Source: www.downbeat-special.co.uk
